article.headline: Weber State beats Northern Colorado 34-21
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- Jadrian Clark passed for three touchdowns, Bo Bolen ran 27 yards for another score on Saturday, and Weber State beat Northern Colorado 34-21. Making his fourth start for the Wildcats (2-9, 2-5 Big Sky), Clark was 16 of 25 for 251 yards and two interceptions, with scoring passes of 14 and 33 yards to Kamana Kaimikaua, and 16 yards to Cameron Livingston for a 21-7 second-quarter lead. Bolen's 143 yards on 25 carries brings him to 2,073 career rushing yards, making him the ninth player in Weber State history with 2,000 career rushing yards. Sean Rubalcaba threw three TD passes -- all to Dimitri Stimphil -- and was 27 of 39 for 305 yards with an interception and a fumble that led to a Weber State score. The Bears (3-7, 2-5) scored on their opening drive, but trailed 24-14 at halftime on a 35-yard field goal by Josh Kealamakia.
